Author::::Maritz
DateTime::::2016-03-08T21:32:33Z
If a genetic abnormality is so catastrophic a miscarriage is the result no improvement in the uterine lining will prevent it. When such a miscarriage occurs it does so because the embryo stopped developing (pre-heartbeat) or died (post-heartbeat). When the embryo dies the body expels the tissue, and sometimes it must be forcibly removed. There is no "resuscitating" it, regardless of how and when it leaves the woman's body.



