Author::::Hugh Easton
DateTime::::2016-03-08T14:34:41Z
The link to cancer was first announced in 1971. Up until that time, as far as the public (and most doctors) knew, DES was a safe and effective treatment (although there had actually been numerous problems seen in animal testing right from the outset, and a large case-controlled study published in 1953, and several subsequent studies, showing that it was completely ineffective at preventing miscarriages). 



